snippet.textDisplay:
LA is not just "starting to embrace diversity" when it's been the epitome of diversity for the country since the city's inception into the Union! It has "literally" most all the biggest ethnic enclaves outside each respective foreign country. What the fuck??!

On top of which my friends in the Valley are mixed Mexican/Cambodian , Filipino/Mexican, Armenian/Filipino, Filipino /Indian, Persian /Spanish , Filipino/African American. (In DC where I lived for 4 years we got dirty looks for being in a mixed relationship.)

Also there's a Mexican Ethiopian restaurant in Sylmar, there's a Mexican Sri Lankan restaurant in Northridge. Kogi is a Mexican Korean taco truck which existed before you even set foot in this city.

And for anyone who thinks this shouldn't be taken personally. Just think about how much backlash this girl would get for saying the same negative, narrow-minded, ignorant stereotypes of people in Mexico, Africa, or Asia. SMH.
